axillary bud : hidden growth point located at the node, right where the leaf meets the stem (axil).
👉 In simple terms:
It’s the “backup plant” sitting at every node

petiole (leaf stem)

🌱 Branching control
Normally stays dormant
Controlled by hormones:

Auxin (from top) suppresses it
→ this is called apical dominance

Cut a single node section
Let it dry (callus) for a few hours


🔥 What activates it?
Triggers:
Cutting the top (reduces auxin)
Damage to main stem
Good light + humidity
Cytokinin increase

👉 Then:
Dormant bud → wakes up → grows


# 🌿 AROID PROPAGATION + HORMONES (CHEAT SHEET)

## 🔑 CORE
- Node + Axillary bud = 🌱 new plant  
- ❌ No node → ❌ no growth  

---

## 🌱 METHODS

### ✂️ Node Cutting
- Top 🔝 = ⚡ fast  
- Mid ➖ = 🐢 slow  
- Needs: node + bud  

---

### 🪵 Wet Stick
- Node only (no leaf)  
- Medium: moss / perlite  
- Needs: 💧 moisture + 🌡️ warmth + 🌫️ humidity  
- Risk: ☠️ rot  

---

### 🌳 Air Layering
- Root before cutting  
- Wrap node with moss 🎁  
- ✅ success ↑↑  
- ❌ risk ↓  

---

### 💧 Water Propagation
- Easy 👍  
- Roots = weak (water type)  
- ⚠️ transplant shock  

---

### 🌿 Moss (BEST)
- ⚖️ air + moisture balance  
- Roots = 💪 strong  

---

### ⚪ Perlite / LECA
- 🫧 oxygen ↑  
- ☠️ rot ↓  
- ⚠️ add nutrients  

---

### 🌱 Division
- Split root clumps  
- Instant plants ⚡  
- Example: Spathiphyllum wallisii  

---

## 🌡️ CONDITIONS
- 🌡️ Temp: 20–30°C  
- 🌫️ Humidity: 70–90%  
- 🌞 Light: bright indirect  

---

## ⚗️ HORMONES (CONTROL)

### 🌿 Auxin (IAA)
- ↑ roots 🌱  
- ↑ apical dominance 🔝  
- ↓ side buds  

---

### 🌱 Cytokinin
- ↑ branching 🌿  
- ↑ bud activation  

---

### 🌳 Gibberellin
- ↑ elongation 📏  
- Low light → stretching  

---

### 🍂 ABA (Abscisic Acid)
- ↑ stress 🛑  
- ↓ growth  
- closes stomata 🚫💧  

---

### 🍎 Ethylene
- ↑ aging 🍂  
- ↑ leaf drop  

---

### 🛡️ Jasmonic Acid
- defense 🐛  

---

### 🦠 Salicylic Acid
- immunity 🛡️  

---

## 🔁 HORMONE TRICKS

- ✂️ Cut top → Auxin ↓ → Cytokinin ↑ → 🌿 buds activate  
- 🌫️ High humidity → rooting ↑ 🌱  
- 🌞 Low light → Gibberellin ↑ → 📏 stretch  

---

## ⚠️ FAIL REASONS
- ❌ No node  
- ❌ Too wet → rot  
- ❌ Too dry → no growth  
- ❌ Low humidity  
- ❌ Cold temperature  

---

## 🧠 MEMORY LINE
- Node = life 🧠  
- Auxin = roots & top 🔝  
- Cytokinin = branching 🌿  
- Balance = success ⚖️
